Files containing the implementation of App\Http\Controllers\Admin\UserController (relative to project root)

- app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php

Explanation
- routes/admin.php imports App\Http\Controllers\Admin\UserController and registers resource routes for users limited to index, edit and update.
- The controller implementation lives at app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php. It defines the handlers used by those routes:
  - index(): returns the users index view (maps to GET /admin/users or /users depending on route prefix; resource index).
  - edit(User $user): returns the edit form view for a given user (maps to GET /users/{user}/edit).
  - update(UsersRequest $request, User $user): processes updates (maps to PUT/PATCH /users/{user}).
- There are other UserController classes in the codebase (e.g. app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/UserController.php and app/Http/Controllers/UserController.php) but they are in different namespaces and are not the controller referenced by routes/admin.php, so they are not listed as handlers for the admin /users routes.
